1
00:00:05,148 --> 00:00:07,807
So I knew some devotees, 
they thought

2
00:00:07,807 --> 00:00:10,968
that you 
put on headphones,

3
00:00:10,968 --> 00:00:13,673
listen to Kṛṣṇa-nām, 
or the Bhāgavatam,

4
00:00:13,673 --> 00:00:17,331
and then wake up 
enlightened.

5
00:00:17,815 --> 00:00:20,972
[Spirit Over Matter]

6
00:00:21,372 --> 00:00:24,851
It’s not a question  of having ­‘muzak’.

7
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:31,223
We have Kṛṣṇa conscious ‘muzak’,
and then wallpaper, 
 

8
00:00:31,223 --> 00:00:33,485
and just 
surrounding yourself

9
00:00:33,485 --> 00:00:39,562
with external paraphernalia 
that that will induce

10
00:00:39,562 --> 00:00:44,223
some sort 
of spiritual awakening.

11
00:00:44,223 --> 00:00:47,679
bhaktyā sañjātayā bhaktyā 
[SB: 11.3.31]:

12
00:00:47,679 --> 00:00:52,932
only devotion
can ignite devotion in another.

13
00:00:53,334 --> 00:00:57,167
There’s no formula,
no method,

14
00:00:57,167 --> 00:01:00,051
no step and 
repeat procedure,

15
00:01:00,051 --> 00:01:04,741
that will generate
spiritual substance.

16
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:10,478
So, Guru Mahārāj’s point
was that

17
00:01:10,939 --> 00:01:15,866
no amount of finite
can generate the infinite.

18
00:01:16,172 --> 00:01:20,334
Matter 
cannot generate spirit,

19
00:01:20,334 --> 00:01:25,302
but spirit 
can manipulate matter.

20
00:01:25,727 --> 00:01:30,003
Spirit can 
express itself through,

21
00:01:31,747 --> 00:01:35,657
but not that 
by reconfiguring the mundane

22
00:01:35,657 --> 00:01:39,586
we can achieve 
the spiritual.

23
00:01:41,048 --> 00:01:43,460
In the Prayers of
the Personified Veda,

24
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:45,515
the 87th chapter 
of the 10th Canto,

25
00:01:45,515 --> 00:01:46,861
this question occurs:

26
00:01:46,861 --> 00:01:53,004
that if we’re using 
the fleshy tongue,

27
00:01:53,004 --> 00:01:58,183
and the voice box, and the body,
to vibrate sound

28
00:01:58,183 --> 00:02:02,847
—Vedas are supposed 
to be spiritual sound—

29
00:02:02,847 --> 00:02:07,820
how can we vibrate 
spiritual sound

30
00:02:08,113 --> 00:02:13,296
if we’re using 
mundane elements?

31
00:02:13,809 --> 00:02:16,759
And this has to do 
with the nature

32
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:20,262
of what is
genuinely spiritual.

33
00:02:22,145 --> 00:02:23,534
Guru Mahārāj 
liked to quote
 

34
00:02:23,534 --> 00:02:25,704
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur 
in Śaraṇāgati,

35
00:02:25,704 --> 00:02:28,202
where it says,
“When the heart

36
00:02:28,202 --> 00:02:31,975
is under the influence
of Kṛṣṇa conception,

37
00:02:32,651 --> 00:02:36,840
the power of the influence 
of that conception

38
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:41,292
comes outwards from the heart
and expresses itself as sound.”

39
00:02:41,315 --> 00:02:45,045
Not that we make a sound,
we say “Hare Kṛṣṇa”,

40
00:02:45,045 --> 00:02:49,784
listen to that sound,
and then it purifies our hearts.

41
00:02:50,241 --> 00:02:53,592
Rather, the heart 
under the influence

42
00:02:53,592 --> 00:02:56,471
of Sādhu, Śāstra, 
Guru, Vaiṣṇava,

43
00:02:56,471 --> 00:02:58,533
expresses spiritual sound.

